    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "LegacyChargeToFiscalYear",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to determine the fiscal year associated with a given legacy charge date. Scalar functions return a single value, and this function is used to map a date to its corresponding fiscal year, which is crucial for financial reporting and analysis."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity level of this function is considered medium. While the logic to determine a fiscal year from a date is straightforward, the function involve date calculations and conditional logic that require a solid understanding of fiscal year definitions and date manipulation in SQL."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@ChargeDate (DATETIME)",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": This parameter represents the date of the legacy charge. It is used to calculate the fiscal year. The fiscal year not align with the calendar year, depending on the organization's fiscal calendar."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "4. Return Type"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "INT",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The function returns an integer representing the fiscal year. This integer is derived from the input date and reflects the fiscal year in which the charge date falls."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "5. Business Logic and Workflow"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The function's business logic involves:"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Determining the fiscal year based on the input charge date."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The fiscal year calculation involve checking the month and day of the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@ChargeDate",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " to decide if it falls in the current or next fiscal year."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "For example, if the fiscal year starts on a date other than January 1st, the function will adjust the year accordingly. If the fiscal year starts on July 1st, a charge date of June 30th, 2023, would belong to fiscal year 2023, while a charge date of July 1st, 2023, would belong to fiscal year 2024."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "6. Performance Considerations"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Scalar functions can have performance implications, especially if used in SELECT statements that process large datasets. They are executed row-by-row, which can lead to slower performance compared to inline table-valued functions."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "To mitigate performance issues, consider using this function in scenarios where it is applied to a limited number of rows or as part of a batch process rather than in high-frequency transactional queries."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "7. Potential Issues or Risks"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Date Handling",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": Incorrect handling of date boundaries can lead to incorrect fiscal year calculations. Ensure that the logic correctly accounts for the start and end of the fiscal year."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Performance",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": As a scalar function, it may introduce performance bottlenecks in queries processing large datasets. Consider alternatives if performance becomes an issue."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Fiscal Year Changes",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": If the organization's fiscal year definition changes, the function must be updated accordingly to reflect the new fiscal year start and end dates."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "8. Function Definition"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "codeBlock",
      "attrs": {
        "language": "sql"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "CREATE  FUNCTION [dbo].[LegacyChargeToFiscalYear] (@JulToDate varchar(5))\nRETURNS varchar(4) AS  \r\nBEGIN \r\ndeclare @FromFiscalYear varchar(6)\r\ndeclare @ToFiscalYear varchar(6)\r\ndeclare @FiscalYear1 varchar(6)\r\ndeclare @FiscalYear2 varchar(6)\r\ndeclare @IsSplit varchar(1)\r\ndeclare @FromDate varchar(8)\r\ndeclare @ToDate varchar(8)\r\n--\r\n--  [dbo].[CreateFiscalYear] (@YYYYMM varchar(6),@Current varchar(1))  \r\n--\r\nset @ToDate = [dbo].[JulianDateToYYYYMMDD] (@JulToDate)\r\n--\r\nset @ToFiscalYear     = substring(@ToDate,1,6) \r\nselect   @FiscalYear2 = [dbo].[CreateFiscalYear] (@ToFiscalYear,'C')  \r\n--\r\nreturn @FiscalYear2\r\nEND"
        }
      ]
    }
